author: Alec Currie
title: Confused about Autograder Feedback: Out of Time
question:
Hi, I have a solution to PSet 9 that passes all of my check expects, however I get this message from the autograder:
Test validity (matches problem statement): error evaluating test operands or expected results: with-limit: out of time.
I have no idea what this means. I'm confident there's no infinite recursion in my code, and all my code follows the templates. What do I need to fix about my code to not get this error?
Thank you
-Alec
student_answer: I believe this shows a bug, suggesting a long-running expression in your code so the function doesn't stop causing the autograder to force it to stop = out of time. Perhaps review your recursion expressions?
